The paper discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN) for generating discrete data, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on image generation and inpainting, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses anomaly detection, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
